# Commit Message Template
#
# Format: <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# Tests: ✅ <passing>/<total> passing
# Breaking Changes: <yes/no>
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Types:
#   feat     - New feature
#   fix      - Bug fix
#   docs     - Documentation only
#   style    - Code style (formatting, missing semi colons, etc)
#   refactor - Code change that neither fixes a bug nor adds a feature
#   perf     - Performance improvement
#   test     - Adding or updating tests
#   chore    - Maintenance tasks
#   build    - Build system or external dependencies
#   ci       - CI/CD configuration
#
# Scope examples:
#   auth, tenders, admin, database, api, frontend, backend
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# BEFORE COMMITTING:
#   1. Run: npm run test:verify
#   2. Verify: All 349 tests passing
#   3. Run: npm run lint
#   4. Check: No console.logs or debug code
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Example:
#
# feat(tenders): add status filtering
#
# - Added status dropdown to tender list
# - Updated TenderList component with filter state
# - Added tests for active/closed/draft statuses
# - All existing tests still passing
#
# Tests: ✅ 352/352 passing
# Breaking Changes: no
#
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
